                    "@type": "Answer",
                    text: "The L33 was used in the Chevrolet TrailBlazer SS (2006–2007), SSR (2005–2006), and Silverado 1500 with VortecMax package (2005–2007). It was also available in the GMC Sierra 1500. All applications feature longitudinal mounting and are part of the GMT800/GMT900 platform family. It does not appear in passenger cars or smaller SUVs.",
